text: Harry Kenneth Lister (1915-2006) was a male athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== Lister represented England in the long jump at the 1938 British Empire Games in Sydney, New South Wales, Australia. ==Personal life== He was a by school teacher by trade and lived at Bromley Wood Lane, in Scunthorpe during 1938. ==References== Category:1915 births Category:2006 deaths Category:English male long jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1938 British Empire Games
